<p>The <strong>Charity board</strong> is the body of the Brotherhood tasked with <strong>promoting, coordinating and overseeing</strong> the corporation’s charitable action. It acts on behalf of all members so that help for those in greatest need is <strong>orderly, prudent and Gospel-shaped</strong>: it curbs improvisation, aligns criteria for requests received by the Brotherhood and reports to the <strong>Governing Board</strong> on main lines of work and significant decisions, while staying close to people who suffer in the <strong>San Pedro</strong> neighbourhood and the parish.</p>
<h2>Main responsibilities</h2>
<p>Its duties typically include the <strong>confidential assessment</strong> of requests for financial or material aid; proposing grants, referrals to <strong>Caritas</strong> or other services when appropriate, or reasoned refusal; monitoring <strong>campaigns</strong> agreed with charitable work; and supporting assistance work and volunteers logistically. The board does not replace the parish priest or public institutions, but it does ensure the Brotherhood responds <strong>coherently</strong> to those who turn to it.</p>
